 6, 7, 8, 9, 10)]\" source_file=\"feedbax/train.py\" source_line=354\n\t\tXLA Label: fusion\n\t\tShape: f32[10,10,10,10,10,10,10,10,10,10,1]\n\t\t==========================\n\n\tBuffer 2:\n\t\tSize: 3.72GiB\n\t\tEntry Parameter Subshape: f32[10,10,10,10,10,10,10,10,10,1]\n\t\t==========================\n```\n\nOn each call to `train_step`, an extra dimension is added to the array parameter of the intervenor, until the array is large enough to cause the OOM error. I don't know yet why this happens.","files":null}]}